# Files scanned by governance-consistency.test.sh for the retired auto-spawn norm.
# One repo-relative path per line; text after '#' is a comment.
#
# Extend this list with any PROJECT-LOCAL doc that could carry the retired norm so
# coverage tracks your repo. Do NOT add files that merely *describe* the retired
# norm (e.g. CHANGELOG.md, AI/decisions.md, the upgrade playbook) — they quote the
# old wording deliberately and would false-positive.
#
# Entries may be literal repo-relative paths OR globs (* ? []). A glob is expanded
# against the repo root (no match -> nothing scanned, never the literal pattern), so
# a whole surface can be covered and future files under it are scanned automatically.
#
# Delete this file to fall back to the script's built-in default list.

MEMORY.md
AI.md
CLAUDE.md
AGENTS.md
.github/copilot-instructions.md
.claude/agents/README.md
.codex/agents/README.md
.github/agents/README.md
INIT.md
docs/collaboration-playbook.md

# SME surfaces — operative, norm-bearing docs that instruct agent behavior. Globbed
# so every current and future SME charter + launcher is scanned automatically. These
# are NOT describe-the-norm files (unlike CHANGELOG/decisions/playbook above), so
# they must stay clean of the retired auto-spawn phrasing.
minions/smes/*.md
.claude/agents/sme-*.md
.codex/agents/sme-*.toml
.github/agents/sme-*.agent.md
